   "source": [
    "# Analyze a Pulsar"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "3ee26eeb-0c5e-4885-9d04-2626ecabd61b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We'll consider Pulsar J1705-1906\n",
    "pulse_f0 = 3.344622243443\n",
    "pulse_dm = 22.907"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "5b37132d-618b-4314-b126-1d99a5fe5ed4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess\n",
    "import tempfile\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "\n",
    "from will import detect"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "82e051c1-16fb-4d24-8606-c780262fc19a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get a 8.1GB filbterbank from zenodo, put it in\n",
    "# a temp directory\n",
    "# This is a slow process\n",
    "temp_dir = tempfile.TemporaryDirectory()\n",
    "j1705 = temp_dir.name + \"/J1705-1906.fil\"\n",
    "r = requests.get(\"https://zenodo.org/record/6481929/files/J1705-1906.fil\")\n",
    "with open(j1705, \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(r.content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b71d2747-d7f3-4cd5-bbfc-837393c5e09b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "detect.find_first_pulse(\n",
    "    file=j1705,\n",
    "    dm=pulse_dm,\n",
    "    box_car_length=16,\n",
    "    start=0,\n",
    "    gulp=2048,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "18b90b73-2bcc-4be3-aec7-79dfad475112",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This give us the location of the first pulse, we can\n",
    "then use this to find all the subsequent pulses because\n",
    "we know the period."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "da88455e-0834-49b4-9f44-351d966cc9f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "params = detect.PulseSearchParamters(\n",
    "    file=j1705,\n",
    "    first_pulse=1035,\n",
    "    period=1 / pulse_f0,\n",
    "    dm=pulse_dm,\n",
    "    box_car_length=16,\n",
    "    samples_around_pulse=900,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,

   "source": [

  },
